Li Ka Shing Knowledge Institute 
The Keenan Research CentreThe Li Ka Shing International Healthcare Education Centre


We create knowledge and narrow the gap between insight and impact.
Our researchers, educators, and front-line clinicians come together in a hospital setting to create, instil, and quickly mobilize health science knowledge.



Research
Our research programs explore fundamental mechanisms of disease, and tackle Canadian and global health challenges.
Find out more


Education
Our innovative educators create memorable insights for clinicians, staff, and the next generation of health care leaders.
Find out more

Translation
LKSKI develops leading knowledge translation strategies to help communities reap the benefits of scientific breakthroughs faster.
Find out more


Reports



We ask because we care: The Tri-Hospital + Toronto Public Health Health Equity Data Collection Research Project Report
A vision where health equity is a priority comes with enormous challenges, and as St. Michael's Hospital is part of one of the most socially diverse LHINs -- the Toronto Central LHIN -- we know that the health needs that go along with diversity are great. This report shows some of the highlights of our work in this area.
View the Health Equity Data Collection Research Project Report



Knowledge Translation: From Evidence to Impact 2007-2012
Knowledge Translation: From Evidence to Impact is a
report highlighting a small sample of our achievements
in knowledge translation from the past five years.
View the Knowledge Translation: From Evidence to Impact 2007-2012 (1.9 MB pdf file)




Education Report 2013
Instead of a traditional booklet, the St. Michael’s Education Report 2013 is an interactive, mobile-friendly website featuring videos, stories and infographics. The report highlights the progress that St. Michael’s has made over the past two years in advancing the education of our students, staff, physicians, patients and their families.
View the 2013 Education Report







